    {
      "id": "c33df483-30a9-4e81-b1fe-5c7d6433afb0",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "# Question 2: Implement the insertion sort",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "c33df483-30a9-4e81-b1fe-5c7d6433afb0"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "6701edfc-294d-4a6f-94d9-66f98da321d6",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "import java.util.Arrays;\nvoid insertion_sort(int[] arr) {\n    int n = arr.length;\n    for (int i =1; i< n; i++){\n        int key = arr[i];\n        int j = i-1;\n        while(j>=0 && arr[j]>key){\n            arr[j+1] = arr[j];\n            j = j-1;\n        }\n        arr[j+1]= key;\n    }\n}\n\n// Unit test\nint[] input_arr = {5, 6, 1, 4, 2, 3};\nint[] output_arr = {1,2,3,4,5,6};\ninsertion_sort(input_arr);\nIO.println(Arrays.equals(input_arr, output_arr));",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "java",
        "id": "6701edfc-294d-4a6f-94d9-66f98da321d6",
